‚úÖ Complete Networking Guide (Updated + Missing Parts Added)
üîπ What is Networking?
Networking connects two or more devices so they can communicate, share data, and access resources using wired or wireless media.

üîπ OSI Model (7-Layer Detailed Overview)
1. Application Layer
Provides services to user applications.
Protocols: HTTP/HTTPS, DNS, SMTP, IMAP, FTP, DHCP APIs

2. Presentation Layer
Handles encryption, compression, encoding.
Protocols: SSL/TLS, JPEG, MPEG

3. Session Layer
Handles sessions, synchronisation.
Protocols: RPC, NetBIOS, PPTP

4. Transport Layer
Reliable or fast data delivery.
Protocols: TCP, UDP

TCP Features:

Connection-oriented

3-way handshake

Reliable (ACK, sequence numbers)

Congestion control

UDP Features:

No connection

Fast, no guarantee

Used in DNS, VoIP, streaming

5. Network Layer
Routing and logical addressing.
Protocols: IP, ICMP, ARP, RIP, OSPF, BGP

6. Data Link Layer
Frames, MAC addresses, error detection.
Protocols: Ethernet, PPP

7. Physical Layer
Electrical/optical signals, cables, bits.

üîπ TCP 3-Way Handshake (Very Important)
SYN ‚Üí Client to server

SYN+ACK ‚Üí Server

ACK ‚Üí Client

üîπ TCP 4-Way Termination
FIN

ACK

FIN

ACK

üîπ TCP vs UDP
Feature	TCP	UDP
Reliability	Yes	No
Speed	Slower	Faster
Ordering	Yes	No
Use Cases	Web, Email	DNS, Gaming, VoIP
üîπ ARP, DHCP, DNS Working (Missing earlier)
ARP (Address Resolution Protocol)
Maps IP ‚Üí MAC inside LAN.

DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)
Provides IP, subnet mask, gateway, DNS dynamically.

DORA:

Discover

Offer

Request

Acknowledge

DNS (Domain Name System)
Converts domain ‚Üí IP.
Query flow: Resolver ‚Üí Root ‚Üí TLD ‚Üí Authoritative server.

üîπ IP Addressing (Complete)
IPv4 Address Structure
32-bit
Example: 192.168.1.10

Network ID + Host ID
Subnet Mask defines the split.

CIDR Notation
/24 means first 24 bits = Network
Common masks:

CIDR	Hosts
/30	2 hosts
/29	6 hosts
/24	254 hosts
/16	65k hosts
üîπ Subnetting (Missing earlier)
Example: 192.168.10.0/24
You want 4 subnets ‚Üí Need +2 bits
New mask: /26
Subnet ranges:

192.168.10.0 ‚Äì 63

192.168.10.64 ‚Äì 127

192.168.10.128 ‚Äì 191

192.168.10.192 ‚Äì 255

üîπ Routing Concepts (Missing earlier)
Static Routing
Manually configured.

Dynamic Routing
Routers learn automatically.

RIP ‚Üí Distance vector

OSPF ‚Üí Link-state

BGP ‚Üí Internet routing

Routing Table Example
Destination  Gateway   Interface
0.0.0.0/0    192.168.1.1   eth0
10.0.0.0/24  0.0.0.0       eth1
üîπ Switching Concepts (Missing earlier)
Switch works in Layer 2.

Switching Types
