Cut-through

Fragment-free

CAM Table
Maps:

MAC ‚Üí Port
STP (Spanning Tree Protocol)
Prevents loops in switched networks.

üîπ VLAN (Very Important)
VLAN logically separates networks inside a switch.

Example:

VLAN 10 ‚Üí Staff

VLAN 20 ‚Üí Guest

802.1Q tagging adds VLAN ID to frames.

üîπ NAT (Network Address Translation) ‚Äî Missing
1. SNAT (Source NAT)
Private ‚Üí Public IP translation.

2. DNAT
Public ‚Üí Private mapping (used in port forwarding).

3. PAT / NAPT
Many private IPs ‚Üí One public IP using ports.

üîπ Network Topologies (Missing)
