Networking Mindmap

Comprehensive Networking Mindmap (Full Detailed + Sequential)
1. Introduction to Networking
Definition: Networking connects devices to share data and resources.

Purpose: Communication, file sharing, remote access, internet.

Components: Devices, media, protocols, services.

Transmission Types:

Wired: Ethernet, Fiber optic, Coaxial.

Wireless: Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, NFC.

Network Types:

LAN: Small area.

WAN: Large geographic area.

MAN: Metropolitan region.

PAN: Personal area.

CAN: Campus.

SAN: Storage.

2. OSI Model (Open Systems Interconnection)
A 7-layer architecture explaining data flow.

2.1 Application Layer (Layer 7)
User-facing network services.

Functions:

Application access

Identity management

Data generation

Protocols: HTTP, HTTPS, DNS, FTP, SMTP, DHCP, SNMP.

2.2 Presentation Layer (Layer 6)
Data formatting, translation.

Functions:

Encryption (SSL/TLS)

Compression (ZIP, MPEG)

Encoding (ASCII, Unicode)

Formats: JPEG, PNG, GIF, MP3, MP4.

2.3 Session Layer (Layer 5)
Manages sessions between applications.

Functions:

Session creation

Authentication

Checkpointing

Protocols: RPC, NetBIOS, PPTP.

2.4 Transport Layer (Layer 4)
End-to-end communication.

Functions:

Segmentation

Flow control

Reliability

Error control

Protocols:

TCP ‚Üí Reliable

UDP ‚Üí Fast, No guarantee

Important: Ports (HTTP-80, DNS-53, HTTPS-443).

2.5 Network Layer (Layer 3)
Logical addressing and routing.

Functions:

Path selection

Packet forwarding

Protocols: IPv4, IPv6, ICMP, ARP, OSPF, RIP, BGP.

Device: Router.

2.6 Data Link Layer (Layer 2)
Physical addressing via MAC.

Functions:

Frame formation

Error detection (CRC)

Protocols: Ethernet, PPP, HDLC.

Devices: Switch, Bridge.

2.7 Physical Layer (Layer 1)
Transmission of binary bits.

Media: Fiber, Copper, Radio waves.

Devices: Hub, Repeater, Cables, NIC.

3. Encapsulation & Decapsulation
Sender Side
Application ‚Üí Data

Transport ‚Üí Data ‚Üí Segment

Network ‚Üí Segment ‚Üí Packet

Data Link ‚Üí Packet ‚Üí Frame

Physical ‚Üí Frame ‚Üí Bits

Receiver Side
Bits ‚Üí Frame ‚Üí Packet ‚Üí Segment ‚Üí Data ‚Üí Application output

4. TCP/IP Model (Alternate To OSI)
Application Layer (Application + Presentation + Session)

Transport Layer (TCP/UDP)

Internet Layer (IP, ICMP)

Network Access Layer (Data Link + Physical)

5. Networking Devices
Layer 1 Devices
Hub ‚Üí Broadcasts to all

Repeater ‚Üí Signal booster

Layer 2 Devices
Switch ‚Üí Uses MAC, forwards frames

Bridge ‚Üí Divides LAN

Access Point ‚Üí Wireless connectivity

Layer 3 Devices
Router ‚Üí Forwards packets using IP

Firewall ‚Üí Controls traffic (Layer 3/4)

Multi-layer Devices
Gateway ‚Üí Converts protocols

Load Balancer

Proxy/Reverse Proxy

6. IP Addressing
IPv4
32-bit

Format: A.B.C.D

Types:

Public

Private

Binary representation

IPv6
128-bit

Hexadecimal format

No need for NAT

Private IP Ranges
Class A: 10.0.0.0/8

Class B: 172.16.0.0/12

Class C: 192.168.0.0/16

IP Classes
A: Large networks

B: Medium

C: Small

D: Multicast

E: Research

7. Subnetting
Splits network into smaller segments.

Steps:

Determine number of hosts/subnets

Decide mask

Calculate:

Network ID

Broadcast ID

Host range

CIDR Notation: /8, /16, /24, etc.

8. Routing
Routing = Finding best path.

Types:
Static

Dynamic

Dynamic Routing Protocols
Distance Vector: RIP

Link State: OSPF

Path Vector: BGP

Routing Concepts
Routing Table

Next Hop

Metric

Administrative Distance

9. Switching Concepts
MAC address learning

Forwarding table (CAM table)

Collision domains

Broadcast domains

VLANs

Trunking (802.1Q)

10. Wireless Networking
Wi-Fi Standards: 802.11a/b/g/n/ac/ax

Frequency bands: 2.4 GHz, 5 GHz, 6 GHz

Encryption: WPA2, WPA3

SSID, BSSID, Channels

11. Network Security
Firewalls (Stateful/Stateless)

IDS/IPS

VPN: IPsec, SSL

ACLs

Proxy servers

DDoS protection

12. NAT (Network Address Translation)
Converts private IPs ‚Üí Public IP

Types:

Static NAT

Dynamic NAT

PAT (Port Address Translation)

13. Load Balancing
Distributes traffic across servers.

Types:

L4 Load Balancing

L7 Load Balancing

Algorithms:

Round Robin

Least Connections

IP Hash

14. Advanced Networking
SDN (Software Defined Networking)

Cloud Networking (VPC, Subnets)

