16. Real-World Data Flow Example
Browser sends HTTP request

Request encapsulated ‚Üí TCP ‚Üí IP ‚Üí Frame

Switch forwards frame

Router forwards packet

Server receives, decapsulates

Response returned back

17. Summary
Networking involves layers, addresses, devices, protocols.

OSI explains how data moves.

TCP/IP is real-world model.

IP addressing/subnetting is foundation.

Switching and routing enable communication.

Security protects the network